President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Kentucky due to severe storms, straight-line winds, tornadoes, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from March 3 to March 4, 2023. This declaration allows for Federal aid to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The designated counties for assistance include Adair, Allen, Anderson, Barren, Bourbon, Breckenridge, Bullitt, and many others. FEMA representative Myra M. Shird has been appointed to coordinate Federal recovery operations. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.